<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!--Transformation version 1.3--><legislativeDoc xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="http://www.lexisnexis.com/xmlschemas/content/public/legislativedoc/1/" schemaVersion="1.0"><legislativeDocHead><citations><citeForThisResource citeDefinition="#7159#349#000064#     2#         1902#">Va. Code Ann. § 64.2-1902</citeForThisResource></citations><legislativeBodyInfo><jurisdiction><jurisSystem normalizedLongName="Virginia" normalizedShortName="VA"/></jurisdiction></legislativeBodyInfo></legislativeDocHead><legislativeDocBody><statute><level levelType="section"><anchor id="_64.2-1902"/><heading><desig>§ 64.2-1902.</desig><title>Nomination of custodian</title></heading><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_a"/><heading><desig>A.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> A person having the right to designate the recipient of property <br/>transferable upon the occurrence of a future event may revocably nominate a <br/>custodian to receive the property for a minor beneficiary upon the occurrence <br/>of the event by naming the custodian followed in substance by the words: "as <br/>custodian for ............… (name of minor) under the Virginia Uniform <br/>Transfers to Minors Act." The nomination may name one or more persons as <br/>substitute custodians to whom the property shall be transferred, in the order <br/>named, if the first nominated custodian dies before the transfer or is unable, <br/>declines, or is ineligible to serve. The nomination may be made in a will, a <br/>trust, a deed, an instrument exercising a power of appointment, or a writing <br/>designating a beneficiary of contractual rights that is registered with or <br/>delivered to the payor, issuer, or other obligor of the contractual rights.</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_b"/><heading><desig>B.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> A custodian nominated under this section shall be a person to whom a transfer of property of that kind may be made under subsection A of <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 64.2-1908"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 64.2-1908">§ 64.2-1908<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000064#     2#         1908#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>.</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_c"/><heading><desig>C.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> The nomination of a custodian under this section does not create custodial property until the nominating instrument becomes irrevocable or a transfer to the nominated custodian is completed under <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 64.2-1908"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 64.2-1908">§ 64.2-1908<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000064#     2#         1908#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>. Unless the nomination of custodian has been revoked, upon the occurrence of the future event the custodianship becomes effective and the custodian shall enforce a transfer of the custodial property pursuant to <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 64.2-1908"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 64.2-1908">§ 64.2-1908<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000064#     2#         1908#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>.</p></bodyText></level><history><historyGroup groupType="history-citation"><historyItem><bodyText><p>1988, c. 516, § 31-39; <citation normalizedCite="2012 VA CH 614"><content><span normalizedCite="2012 Va. Ch. 614">2012, c. 614<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#2012#000614#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>.</p></bodyText></historyItem></historyGroup></history></level></statute></legislativeDocBody><metadata><dc:metadata xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><dc:id